HEADWORD: Boncilate
<hw>Bon"ci*late</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Empirical trade
name.]</ety> <def>A substance composed of ground bone, mineral matters,
etc., hardened by pressure, and used for making billiard balls, boxes,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

